  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Solar Irrigation in Burkina</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">100 women will have the opportunity to significantly increase their market gardening production and household income and  800 people will be more resilient to food shortages and have a more balanced diet. More than 1,000 people will have access to drinking water   100 women will improved their status in the community.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Construction of a solar-powered pump, a drop-by-drop irrigation system, and a water storage tower to irrigate two hectares of market garden (cultivated by 100 women). 
 The installation of solar panels will also provide women with additional livelihood opportunities, such as offering mobile phone charging facilities to generate further income</narrative>
  </description>
